                                 ARTICLES
     =================================================================

          I  have  written two Outside programs for the OPUS <tm>
     and Fido 11w <tm> Bulletin Board Systems.  They may be piped
     (redirected) using the excellent program GATEWAY,  or  using
     DOS redirection through CTTY Com1 or CTTY Com2.

          These  two programs are called TRANSITS and NATAL. They
     are for  the  astrology  student.  (And,  it  seems,  Ronald
     Reagan.)

          When invoked, TRANSITS will calculate the longitude and
     latitude  for  the  Sun,  Moon, planets, five asteroids, and
     eight uranian placements, with heliocentric  and  geocentric
     values, for  the  exact moment TRANSITS is run.  It gets the
     required information  from  the  computer's  date  and  time
     stamp,  and  a  sysop-edited file called TRANSITS.CTL. These
     values will be given in decimal and sign notation.

          TRANSITS.CTL  just  holds  the  geographic   longitude,
     latitude, and time zone for the computer running TRANSITS.

          A  sample  batch  file  is  included with TRANSITS. The
     device driver that does  the  redirection  (piping)  is  NOT
     included,  as  it  is  not  my  program, but is available at
     Astro-Net (Called GATEWAY).    The  carrier  detect  program
     WATCHCD  is  also a good idea, and is available at Astro-Net
     as well.  Please, if you use  the  programs  GATEWAY  and/or
     WATCHCD, pay the shareware price for them.

          TRANSITS  may  be  downloaded  from  Astro-Net  free of
     charge.  It may not be sold for  any  price  or  remittance.
     This  means  "distributing  companies" may not copy and sell
     any of my programs.  TRANSITS may only be installed on a BBS
     that does not charge users for any remittance for using said
     BBS.

          File request: TRANSITS.ARC.

          The program NATAL will do the  same  as  TRANSITS,  but
     requires the  user to supply all information.  The user must
     enter day of event, month, year, time, longitude,  latitude,
     and zone.    NATAL  will  also calculate the Placidian house
     cusps, unlike TRANSITS. NATAL does  not  require  any  other
     file to run, and therefore requires no maintenance.

          Fire Request: NATAL.ARC

          David   Rice  Astro-Net  (1:103/503.0)  (714)  662-2294
     2400,n,8,1.

