     By-Laws and Rules Committee
     1:102/2871

     The By-laws and Rules Committee has prepared the rules which
     appear below for this year's By-laws amendment process.  They
     have been approved by the IFNA Board of Directors.


                 1988 Rules for Amendment of By-laws


     1. By-Law Amendments will only be accepted from IFNA members.

     2. The By-Laws Committee is responsible for any suggested
        changes to the By-Laws.  To this end, all suggestions must be
        submitted to the By-Laws Committee for inclusion on the
        Ballot.  The Committee reserves the right to edit, combine, or
        expand the submissions provided that any changes made do not
        substantially change the original intent of the suggestion.
        In the event of conflicting suggestions, the changes may be
        presented on the Ballot in the form of a "multiple choice"
        where only one of the suggestions may be selected.

     3. All proposed amendments will be of the form "old wording"/
        "new wording" including By-Law reference numbers where
        applicable.  This is intended to clarify the changes proposed.

     4. All changes must be received by the Secretary at least 60
        days prior to the scheduled vote date in order to be included
        on the Ballot.  They will then be forwarded to the By-Laws
        committee for preparation for inclusion on the Ballot.

     5. Ballots will be accepted from members in good standing
        through regular postal service addressed to the Secretary and
        must be received no later than the Annual Meeting.
        Alternately, Ballots will be accepted from members in good
        standing provided they are hand delivered to the Secretary or
        his designate at the Annual Meeting, no later than the
        announced time for the closing of the polls.

     6. A certified public accountant will receive and collate all
        mail Ballots received prior to the Annual Meeting, and will be
        responsible for the receipt, tabulation and verification of
        all Ballots cast before the close of voting.  The certified
        public accountant will present and certify the results of the
        balloting.

     7. In the event of a tie, the current (outgoing) President shall
        cast the deciding vote.

